@*
    This Razor view macro partial displays the latest tweets from a specified Twitter handle.
    - Expects a macro parameter "twitterHandle" (string) to be provided.
    - Renders a Twitter timeline widget for the given handle using Twitter's embedded timeline.
    - The Twitter widget script is loaded asynchronously.
    Usage:
        - Place this macro in a template or content page and provide the "twitterHandle" parameter.
        - Example: twitterHandle = "HighlyDeveloped"
    Note:
        - Ensure the Twitter handle is valid and does not include the '@' symbol.
        - The timeline will be embedded where this macro is rendered.
*@
@inherits Umbraco.Web.Macros.PartialViewMacroPage
@{

    var twitterHandle = Model.MacroParameters["twitterHandle"] as string;
}
<a class="twitter-timeline" href="https://twitter.com/@twitterHandle?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">Tweets by @twitterHandle</a> 
<script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>